Shudufhadzo Musida has been crowned Miss South Africa 2020. JOHANNESBURG - Shudufhadzo Musida has been crowned Miss South Africa 2020. The 24-year-old from Limpopo beat 15 other contestants from across the country to scoop the prestigious crown. READ: Miss Universe Zozibini Tunzi nominated for E! People's Choice Award Musida walks away with a lucrative R3-million prize package. Thato Mosehle is the first runner-up, while Natasha Joubert took the third spot. The pageant was held at the Table Bay hotel in Cape Town and was hosted by South African media personality, Nomzamo Mbatha.